## Rule 5 — Tailwind v4: CSS-First, No tailwind.config.js

Tailwind v4 reads configuration from CSS `@theme` blocks. There is no `tailwind.config.js`. Creating one will be silently ignored.

```css
/* ✅ DO — app/globals.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --font-sans: "Inter", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
  --color-brand-50: oklch(0.97 0.01 250);
  --color-brand-500: oklch(0.55 0.2 250);
  --color-brand-900: oklch(0.25 0.1 250);
  --breakpoint-xs: 30rem;
}

/* shadcn/ui semantic tokens — use @theme inline so they reference CSS vars */
@theme inline {
  --color-background: hsl(var(--background));
  --color-foreground: hsl(var(--foreground));
  --color-primary: hsl(var(--primary));
  --color-primary-foreground: hsl(var(--primary-foreground));
  --color-muted: hsl(var(--muted));
  --color-muted-foreground: hsl(var(--muted-foreground));
  --color-border: hsl(var(--border));
}
```

```js
// ❌ DON'T — tailwind.config.js/ts is Tailwind v3 syntax; ignored in v4
module.exports = {
  content: ["./app/**/*.tsx"],
  theme: { extend: { colors: { brand: "#4f46e5" } } },
};
```

Also: use `@import "tailwindcss"` — not the old v3 directives:

```css
/* ❌ DON'T — v3 directives */
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

